goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the frequency of flight delays and the range of delay times.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between flight distance and delay time?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of distance vs delay
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify if there is a relationship between the distance of a flight and the delay time.

goals.question: What is the average flight duration?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of flight durations and identify any outliers.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight distances?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the frequency of flight distances and the range of distances traveled.

goals.question: What is the relationship between flight duration and distance?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of distance vs time
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify if there is a relationship between the distance of a flight and the duration of the flight.

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean = {data['delay'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median = {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['delay', 'distance']]
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    plt.ylabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between flight distance and delay time?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.boxplot(data['time'])
    plt.title('What is the average flight duration?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Duration (hours)')
    plt.xticks([])
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
